    "---\n",
    "# Part 3: Adaptive Ellipse-Ring Idle Policy\n",
    "\n",
    "When a driver finishes a trip:\n",
    "1. Count `n_active` = number of idle + repositioning drivers\n",
    "2. Compute `n_active` evenly-spaced homes around the 1-sd Mahalanobis ellipse of the pickup distribution\n",
    "3. Assign the driver to the closest available home slot\n",
    "4. If within 0.25 miles of the slot → stay put (no wasted fuel)\n",
    "5. Otherwise, begin repositioning — but remain **interruptible** (if a rider request arrives and this driver is closest, they divert mid-journey to the pickup instead)"
   ]
